SUMMARY:The Zone
DESCRIPTION:\nFreedom of expression is a constitutional right.  \nBut codified freedom and social permission are not the same thing.  \nThis evening by Myān Dance Company unfolds in six segments\, each tracing a different pressure point in the life of a working artist. The need to be seen. The fatigue of hustle culture. Stolen moments of relief. The weight of expectation\, the pull of impulsive choices\, and the complicated fallout of cancel culture. \nThe evening includes an improvisational segment. The audience is asked a question. One response is chosen at random. One dancer interprets it\, unrehearsed\, in movement. \nWhat you accept\, and what you don’t\, is also part of the performance. The stage is only as free as the room allows. \n\n\n\n\n\nCast:\nMukta Nagpal\nAshish Rao\nJyoti Naik\nSasha Shetty\nArchana Gokhale\nAntra Shankar \n\n\n\nSupported by: \n \n\n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/the-zone/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_TZ.jpg
END:VEVENT
