SUMMARY:I\, Poppy
DESCRIPTION:80 minutes | Mewadi and Hindi with English subtitles | India\, France | 2025 \nBlack Gold. Medicine and livelihood. Illegal and industrialised.  \nVardibai farms poppies in rural Rajasthan. Her son\, Mangilal\, organizes protests against the Narcotics Bureau officers who issue licences\, fix crop prices\, and revoke permissions when farmers resist. She tends her fields. He mobilizes crowds. She pays bribes to survive. He fights the system that demands them. \nShot over four years\, I\, Poppy watches a Dalit family caught between two impossible choices: comply and survive\, or resist and risk everything. When Mangilal wins\, Vardibai loses her licence. Then the rains come. \nFilmmaker Vivek Chaudhary joins virtually for a conversation with Sunanda Bhat of Vikalp Bengaluru\, followed by a Q&A with the audience. \nIn collaboration with: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/i-poppy/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Agriculture,Film,Society
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-22-3.jpg
END:VEVENT
